False.<br>
Quad Kiting wizards do not like Swarm Kiting bards.  Both seem to feel they have exclusive rights to soloing limited mobs.<br>
<br>
A grouped Wizard loves a grouped Bard.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Anyways, I didnt know bards can fit in any role of a group.<br>
<br>
Tank, damage dealer and healer are 3 main jobs a bard cannot achieve :P<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Again, false.<br>
- At lower levels, Bards tank as well as anybody.  At higher levels, they can get the job done with the right AAs and the right gear.<br>
- Bards can match Rogue damage output if playing all damage songs while meleeing.  Bards can easily exceed this in AE situations.<br>
- While not the greatest of healers, Bards can get the job done with regen and rune songs.  Especially in an all-Bard group.  (PoP mobs would eat right thru Bard &quot;healing&quot;, but six Bards in Pop would be Charming or kiting anyways). <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Veteran <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=111714">Keiz Dinzyar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
