<br>
Not sure what baggage your talking about? FV ruleset is pretty lax.  We have over time lost alot of the original hassles that seems to annoy people.<br>
<br>
Here is the ruleset and how its been altered. <br>
<br>
 <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>This is a new server, not a split server. There will be no transfers to this server.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
This still holds true except Legends server.<br>
<br>
<br>
·<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> Characters will be wiped before the server goes Live.<br>
· This is a PvE (Player vs. Environment) server, NOT a PvP (Player vs. Player) server. In other words, it's a standard &quot;blue&quot; server with the same rules and features regarding PvP as the vast majority of our servers. It is not one of the &quot;Zeks&quot;.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
The server is now over a year old.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>· Auction restricted to city zones: Qeynos, Surefall Glade, Highkeep, Freeport, Rivervale, Erudin, Halas, Neriak, Grobb, Oggok, Greater Faydark, Ak'Anon, Kaladim, Felwithe, Paineel, Cabilis, Kael and Thurgadin.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
This is pretty much been wiped away as a rule. And the bazaar has pretty much made auctioning pointless anyways.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>· Beneficial buff spells will not work on characters 20 levels lower than the caster.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
True, except splash effect. Basicly, if a enchanter targets themself with KEI they will get you with the splash effect. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>· Each character will be assigned an &quot;alignment&quot; upon creation. This alignment will be described in brief on the character creation screen (in the same location their Deity is described).<br>
· Each character will be able to change their alignment once any time after they reach 10th level if they choose. A character is not required to change alignments, but may do so any time after attaining 10th level. The player will be able to choose from a list of alignments based on their race, class and deity. <br>
· A character's alignment will determine whether or not they can group or guild with other characters. <br>
· A character's alignment will determine an experience bonus or penalty when grouping with other characters. <br>
· A character's alignment will determine if they can cast beneficial spells on other characters (including resurrections).</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
All alignment stuff is gone now from FV.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>· Language skills will improve only through group chat in the same zone and from /say.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
Almost true, they don't improve through use of say. Only grouping and tells. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>· Languages will only improve 1 point each hour and will be capped at level*5+5 skill points.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
Gone, you can just spam someone til they know a language fully.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>· Common will not exist. A Human language will be added and only made easily available to certain races.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
True, though, common has been replaced with Language. Almost everyone by level 5 knows the following languages. <br>
<br>
Human and Elven. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>· One character per account.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
True<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>· The Trivial Loot Code will be in effect in all zones.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
True, though, raid feature circumvents all TLC at the moment.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>· Very few items will be No-Drop. Exceptions will include things such as newbie notes and epic weapons.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
True<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>· Bind Affinity will be restricted for all characters to locations where melee characters can bind on other servers.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
True<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>· /emote will be language specific</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
True<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>· All characters will be /roleplay.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
Gone<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>· /alignment will display the alignment of your character and probably a more detailed description of that alignment.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
All alignment stuff is gone. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
As you can see, they are slowly gutting FV to be a plain blue server with a slightly different ruleset.  As long as they keep the TLC and no No Drop it will still have something to offer. Otherwise, it will just become server 51.<br>
